<ivy-module rev="$Id$">

    <info publication="20120106120000">
        <license name="Apache License, Version 2.0" url="http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0"/>
        <description homepage="http://code.google.com/p/google-diff-match-patch/">
            <p>The Diff Match and Patch libraries offer robust algorithms to perform the operations required for synchronizing plain text. </p>

            <ol>
                <li><strong>Diff:</strong> </li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Compare two blocks of plain text and efficiently return a list of differences. </li>
                    <li><a href="http://neil.fraser.name/software/diff_match_patch/svn/trunk/demos/demo_diff.html">Diff Demo</a> </li>
                </ul>
                <li><strong>Match:</strong> </li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Given a search string, find its best fuzzy match in a block of plain text.  Weighted for both accuracy and location. </li>
                    <li><a href="http://neil.fraser.name/software/diff_match_patch/svn/trunk/demos/demo_match.html">Match Demo</a> </li>
                </ul>
                <li><strong>Patch:</strong> </li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Apply a list of patches onto plain text.  Use best-effort to apply patch even when the underlying text doesn&#x27;t match. </li>
                    <li><a href="http://neil.fraser.name/software/diff_match_patch/svn/trunk/demos/demo_patch.html">Patch Demo</a> </li>
                </ul>
            </ol>

            <p>Currently available in Java, JavaScript, Dart, C++, C#, Objective C, Lua and Python.
            Regardless of language, each library features <a href="/p/google-diff-match-patch/wiki/API">the same API</a> and the same functionality.
            All versions also have comprehensive test harnesses. </p>

            <h3><a name="Algorithms"></a>Algorithms<a href="#Algorithms" class="section_anchor"></a></h3>

            <p>This library implements <a href="http://neil.fraser.name/software/diff_match_patch/myers.pdf">Myer&#x27;s diff algorithm</a>
            which is generally considered to be the best general-purpose diff.  A layer of <a href="http://neil.fraser.name/writing/diff/">pre-diff
            speedups and post-diff cleanups</a> surround the diff algorithm, improving both performance and output quality. </p>

            <p>This library also implements a <a href="http://neil.fraser.name/software/diff_match_patch/bitap.ps">Bitap matching algorithm</a>
            at the heart of a flexible <a href="http://neil.fraser.name/writing/patch/">matching and patching strategy</a>.
            </p>

        </description>
    </info>

    <publications>
        <artifact/>
        <artifact name="source" type="source" ext="zip"/>
        <artifact name="javadoc" type="javadoc" ext="zip"/>
    </publications>

</ivy-module>
